  "updateinfo_id": "ALSA-2026:39180",
  "description": "The kernel-rt packages provide the Real Time Linux Kernel, which enables fine-tuning for systems with extremely high determinism requirements.  \n\nSecurity Fix(es):  \n\n  * kernel: net: bridge: use a stable FDB dst snapshot in RCU readers (CVE-2026-46086)\n  * kernel: xfrm: defensively unhash xfrm_state lists in __xfrm_state_delete (CVE-2026-46116)\n  * kernel: XFS data corruption using reflink ()\n\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n",
  "fromstr": "packager@almalinux.org",
